Package com.example.inventorymanager

Class Item

java.lang.Object
com.example.inventorymanager.Item
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.os.Parcelable
public class Item extends Object implements android.os.Parcelable
A representation of an item within the context of an inventory management system. Stores relevant information about an item (alongside access functions), including:
  • the item's name,
  • a brief description of the item,
  • the date the item was purchased,
  • the model of the item,
  • the make of the item,
  • the serial number of the item,
  • the estimated monetary value of the item,
  • and a comment about the item.
Implements the Parcelable interface to be able to be passed between fragments, as required for filtering items.
Author:
Kareem Assaf, Isaac Joffe, David Onchuru

    • Item

      public Item(String itemName, String purchaseDate, String description, String model, String make, String serialNumber, String estimatedValue, String comment)
      Creates an Item() object with the fields passed in. All inputs are assumed to be valid, as ensured by ItemUtility(). Inputs are validated inside the fragment before this constructor is called.
      Parameters:
      itemName - The name of the item to be created.
      purchaseDate - The date that the item to be created was purchased.
      description - A brief description of the item to be created.
      model - The model of the item to be created.
      make - The make of the item to be created.
      serialNumber - The serial number of the item to be created.
      estimatedValue - The estimated monetary value of the item to be created.
      comment - A brief comment about the item to be created.
